The Velvet Students in concert with the Charles University choirs
The Festival Festival Academica offers for the third time the festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary schools.
The end of the festival consists of two concerts organized on November 17.
“The Charles University has an important part in this festival”
“From the choir there is the Choeur de la Faculté de Pedagogie et des Humanités, in the committee of the festival sits the Rector Vaclav Hamp,” says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The closing of the festival is the Choeur des lycées and secondary classes concert, which takes place with free entry on November 17 from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening there is the concert - Vellum Students - in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools and that of the Charles University occur.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate with dignity the International Student Day and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the velour revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop creative cooperation of young people.
The principal organizer is the Czech Stock Exchange in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, mesical meetings, student happening and other activities.
The interested will find all information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
