For example, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, it may be that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no record of voting and counting in the urn file is not found in the president of the poll; or there are obvious errors or alterations in the minutes.
In addition, the total counting of votes received in all polls may be made when there is an indication that the difference between the alleged candidate winning the respective election and the candidate who obtained the second place in the poll is equal or below a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express petition from the party representative and/or coalition who presented the second of the candidates reported.
The total counting of the ballot may also be achieved if at the end of the common count it is found that the difference between the alleged candidate winning and that of the second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, provided that there is the express petition of the representative of the political party whose candidate emerged second, in which case the electoral packages that have been subject to the partial counting will be excluded.
