Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A Cali dactyloscopeist went to history as the man who confirmed the death of \"Alfonso Cano\".
The work of these staff members is crucial.
Last November 4th, a CTI Dactyloscopeist from Cali passed to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of the Farc: \"Alfonso Cano\" by confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopeists working at the ITC's local offices, this week it was Eliazar González's \"availability tour\", a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working for 21 years in the field of judicial investigation.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the corpses were to be identified.
The year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after having followed adequate courses, he specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was advised to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who was leading the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the dead body, he did not recognize him by his physical appearance, because he was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He did not have a beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtian wolf, ink, a foreman and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not deceive him: it was \"Alfonso Cano\"
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the man who confirmed to the Minister of Defence, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farc.
Searching for the fingerprint
For a Dactyloscopeist from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos has made to Eliazar González in a press conference for the operation against -Cano - is very significant.
A lot of people don't know about our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without margin of error, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
In addition to identifying the corpses, the dactyloscopeists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search the database.
The researcher reported that in a case of theft he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in this place the thief had held his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
\"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to draw a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different flights - he remembers.
The fingerprints may also remove or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently we found him a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a parent may be a suspect of the crime and that an imprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee that he's the killer, it puts him on the crime scene.
A CTI Dactyloscopeist explained that digital fingerprints are extracted from objects with chemical or physical reagents -
When they appear, they are used by a breeder or band to take them.
Thereafter, fingerprints are sent to Asif, the declinent database, or to the National Civil Registry.
\"The problem is that there are still a lot of undocumented Colombians,\" said the expert from the ITC.
He explained that everything is not how we show it in the CSI television program.
As everything that shines is not gold, all that is touched does not become necessarily an imprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
